          <div class="coach-bd">One of the highest-impact interventions. Timely, specific feedback on the task — not the person — dramatically increases student achievement. For teachers: model giving feedback in lesson debrief.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="coach-card">
          <div class="coach-hd"><div style="font-size:12.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text)">TLAC: Cold Call (Technique 22)</div><span class="res-tag rt-tlac">TLAC</span></div>
          <div class="coach-bd">Call on students regardless of hand-raising. Normalizes participation for all students and maintains academic accountability throughout independent and whole-group work. Maps to MO Standard 5.2.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="coach-card">
          <div class="coach-hd"><div style="font-size:12.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text)">Marzano: Cooperative Learning (Element 25)</div><span class="res-tag rt-marzano">Marzano</span></div>
          <div class="coach-bd">Structured group work with individual accountability increases engagement and content mastery. Map to MO Standards 4.3 and 5.2. Pair with an accountability artifact — exit slip, sticky note, turn-and-talk.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
