<div class="panel" id="panel-privacy">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-tag">Data Protection</div>
    <div class="hero-title">Privacy & Zero Data Retention</div>
    <div class="hero-sub">Built for zero liability — not by policy, but by architecture. Here's exactly what that means.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid2 mb16">
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">🎓 FERPA</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">FERPA is triggered when student education records are stored or transmitted to a third party persistently. This tool never stores a student record. Uploading a gradebook PDF here is functionally identical to opening it in your browser — FERPA does not regulate that. No student name, ID, or score ever touches a server in a stored state.</div></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">👩‍🏫 MNEA / MSTA Union</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">Teacher unions have concerns about observation data in district-controlled systems that can be subpoenaed. None of that applies here. Observation notes, eval progress, and coaching records exist only in your session. There is no district-controlled database. There is nothing to subpoena. This tool is a smart notepad — not a surveillance system.</div></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">⚖️ HR Exposure</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">HR issues arise when informal notes about employees exist in accessible systems. Because nothing is stored between sessions, there is no repository of draft observations or coaching notes that anyone else could access — not your principal, not HR, not a district administrator. Your notes are yours until you choose to formally transmit them through official channels.</div></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">☁️ What the AI Sees</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">When you request AI-generated content, your text is sent to Claude via an encrypted Cloudflare Worker. Claude processes it and returns a response. The Worker does not log, store, or transmit content elsewhere. Use role-based labels ("3rd Grade ELA teacher") rather than real names in AI prompts.</div></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">💻 Personal Device</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">Use this tool on a personal device on personal wifi — not a district-owned device on the school network. District IT monitoring can see network traffic on school equipment. Since this is your personal tool at your personal URL, using it on a personal device is the natural use case.</div></div>
    <div class="card"><div class="card-hd"><div class="card-title">🏫 Changing Schools</div></div><div class="card-bd" style="font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--text-mid)">Because nothing from any school is ever stored, no data carries over when you move. When you update School Setup, you only change a display name and colors. No student records, eval history, or coaching notes transfer — because none of it was ever retained. Clean slate every time.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="ai-box" style="margin-top:0">
    <strong>30-second explanation for administrators:</strong><br>
    "This tool is a browser-based smart notepad. It helps me analyze data and draft documents, but it stores nothing. The moment I close the tab, everything is gone — no database, no server history, no retained records. It's the same as using a PDF reader — nothing persists unless I explicitly save and send it through official channels."
  </div>
</div>

