let incidents = [];

const BEHAVIOR_SYSTEM = `You are an expert in Missouri Schoolwide Positive Behavior Support (MO SW-PBS) Tier 1, Tier 2, and Tier 3 behavior intervention systems, working as an AI coaching partner for an Administrator at a PreK-5 elementary school in Northwest R-I School District, Dittmer, Missouri.

COMPLETE MO SW-PBS KNOWLEDGE BASE:

TIER 1 (Universal — All Students):
- 3–5 OMPUA schoolwide expectations (Observable, Measurable, Positively stated, Understandable, Always applicable)
- Behavior matrix across settings; acknowledgment system (90%+ staff / 50%+ students)
- Staff-managed vs. office-managed (ODR) definitions with discipline flowchart
- Big 5 data: ODRs by incident type, behavior, location, time of day, student — reviewed monthly
- 8 Effective Classroom Practices; TIPS meeting minutes; Working Smarter template
- TFI Tier 1: 15 items (Teams 1.1–1.2, Implementation 1.3–1.11, Evaluation 1.12–1.15), target 70%+

TIER 2 (Targeted — ~15% of students):
- Identification: 2+ of: data decision rules (2–5 ODRs), teacher/parent nomination, universal screening
- Data decision rules: Positive→continue/fade; Questionable→check fidelity→modify; Poor→verify fidelity→intensify or Tier 3 referral
- Threshold: 4 consecutive weeks, 4+ data points/week at 80%+
- CICO (Check-In, Check-Out / BEP): DPR scoring (3=0–1 reminders, 2=2 reminders, 1=3+)
- SSIG/SGSS: Social Skills Intervention Group — function-matched small group
- Self-Monitoring: student observes/records own behavior, goal setting, self-evaluation, fading to independence
- Check & Connect (U of MN): K–12 disengagement/dropout risk, mentoring + regular check-ins
- FIRST STEP Next: PreK–2 defiance, peer conflicts, disruptive behavior
- CW-FIT: Class-Wide Function-Related Intervention Teams — group contingency
- Tootling: peer-mediated positive reporting
- FACTS Part A: 9-section tool for function hypothesis
- TFI Tier 2: 13 items (Teams 2.1–2.4, Interventions 2.5–2.9, Evaluation 2.10–2.13), target 80%+

BEHAVIOR FUNCTIONS (ABC Framework):
- Setting Event → Antecedent → Behavior → Consequence → Function
- OBTAIN (positive reinforcement): Get Adult Attention, Get Peer Attention, Access Activities/Tangibles, Sensory/Stimulation
- ESCAPE/AVOID (negative reinforcement): Avoid Adult Attention, Avoid Peer Attention, Avoid Tasks, Avoid Stimuli
- NOT functions: revenge, control, anger management
- Frequency scale: 1=monthly, 2=weekly, 3=2–3x/week, 4=daily, 5=3–4x/day, 6=every hour
- Behavior Intensity: Level 1 (confined to student) → Level 5 (threatens physical injury)

TIER 3 (Intensive — ~5% of students):
- FBA 6-Step Process: (1) Student ID by Core Team (2) Notify Action Team (3) Record review: ODRs, attendance, academic, health, IEP (4) Interviews: homeroom, referrer, other staff, family, student (5) Summary Statement: observable behavior + antecedent + consequence + setting event + function (6) ABC observation in problem AND non-problem routines, confirm summary statement
- BIP 7 Sections: Competing Behavior Pathway, Intervention Strategies (setting event + antecedent + teaching + consequence), Safety Plan, Implementation Plan, Monitoring & Evaluation, Generalization & Maintenance — requires signatures
- Competing Pathway: long-term replacement (same function, incompatible, observable) + short-term alternate + reinforcing consequence matching function
- Safety Planning: 7 phases (Calm→Trigger→Agitation→Acceleration→Crisis/Peak→De-escalation→Recovery), staff responses per phase
- Progress monitoring: baseline before intervention; DPR method; fading to self-monitoring = graduation

MENU OF FUNCTION-BASED INTERVENTIONS:
Seek Attention function: Increase positive recognition, give leadership role, increase OTR, increase peer interaction, teach how to ask for attention appropriately, respond quickly when asks appropriately, give frequent attention for appropriate behavior
Avoid Attention function: Cooperative group assignment, preferential seating, visual schedule, preview upcoming tasks, teach self-management (observing/recording/goal setting/evaluating), acknowledge with nonverbal reinforcements (thumbs up, small note)
Avoid Tasks function: Teach asking for help, pre-teach content, modify amount/type, provide choice, sequence tasks (preferred first), teach how to ask for break or alternative, address task difficulty, offer brief assistance, provide consistent calm response

DATA COLLECTION:
- Event Recording: frequency/rate, low freq short duration
- Duration Recording: moderate-long duration behaviors
- Latency: time between prompt and compliance
- Partial Interval: low frequency, any duration
- Whole Interval: high freq, moderate-long duration
- Momentary Time Sampling: high freq, short duration
- Permanent Product (DPR): student earns points on BIP
- 40 intervals / 20-minute observation format standard

DISTRICT CONTEXT:
- Northwest R-I School District, Dittmer MO — Maple Grove Elementary K-5
- IBN (Individual Behavior Notification) rights for students with IEPs regarding discipline — 10-day cumulative threshold triggers manifestation determination, family notification required
- RSMo 167.161: board may suspend/expel for conduct prejudicial to good order; principal can remove immediately if threat of harm; prior discipline cannot be SOLE basis; students with disabilities have additional procedural rights
- No real student names, DOBs, or identifiers — always use anonymized student codes
- FERPA applies — never store or transmit personally identifiable student information
- All data is session-only, zero retention architecture

PBIS DATA-BASED DECISION MAKING (6-Step DBDM):
1. Collect & Chart  2. Analyze & Prioritize  3. SMART Goals  4. Select Strategies  5. Results Indicators  6. Evaluate

Your role: Analyze behavioral data provided, identify patterns using MO SW-PBS decision rules, recommend evidence-based interventions matched to behavior function and tier, and draft practical communications. Be specific, actionable, and grounded in MO SW-PBS. Always use anonymized codes only — never request or use real student names.`;

function getBehaviorSummaryText() {
  if (!incidents.length) return 'No incidents logged yet.';
  const lines = incidents.map(i =>
    `[${i.date} ${i.time}] Code:${i.code} Grade:${i.grade} Behavior:${i.type} Location:${i.location} Antecedent:${i.antecedent} Response:${i.response} Severity:${i.severity} Staff:${i.staff} ParentContacted:${i.parentContact} IEP:${i.iep} Notes:${i.notes}`
  );
  return lines.join('\n');
}

function getStudentIncidents(code) {
  return incidents.filter(i => i.code.trim().toLowerCase() === code.trim().toLowerCase());
}

function logIncident() {
  const code = document.getElementById('beh-code').value.trim();
  const grade = document.getElementById('beh-grade').value;
  const date = document.getElementById('beh-date').value;
  const time = document.getElementById('beh-time').value;
  const type = document.getElementById('beh-type').value;
  const location = document.getElementById('beh-location').value;
  const antecedent = document.getElementById('beh-antecedent').value.trim();
  const response = document.getElementById('beh-response').value.trim();
  const staff = document.getElementById('beh-staff').value.trim();
  const severity = document.getElementById('beh-severity').value;
  const parentContact = document.getElementById('beh-parent-contact').checked;
  const iep = document.getElementById('beh-iep').checked;
  const notes = document.getElementById('beh-notes').value.trim();

  if (!code || !type || !date) { showToast('Please enter student code, behavior type, and date.'); return; }

  const incident = { id: Date.now(), code, grade, date, time, type, location, antecedent, response, staff, severity, parentContact, iep, notes };
  incidents.push(incident);

  // Reset form
  ['beh-code','beh-antecedent','beh-response','beh-staff','beh-notes'].forEach(id => document.getElementById(id).value = '');
  ['beh-grade','beh-type','beh-location','beh-severity'].forEach(id => document.getElementById(id).value = '');
  document.getElementById('beh-parent-contact').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('beh-iep').checked = false;

  renderIncidentLog();
  updateBehaviorStats();
  updateBadge('badge-behavior', incidents.length);
  syncMobBehaviorBadge(incidents.length);
  showToast('Incident logged ✓');
}

function renderIncidentLog() {
  const el = document.getElementById('beh-log-list');
  if (!el) return;
  const filterVal = (document.getElementById('beh-filter')?.value || '').toLowerCase();
  const filtered = filterVal ? incidents.filter(i => i.code.toLowerCase().includes(filterVal)) : incidents;

  if (!filtered.length) {
    el.innerHTML = '<div style="color:var(--muted);font-size:12.5px;text-align:center;padding:20px">No incidents logged yet. Use the form to add an incident.</div>';
    return;
  }

  const sevColor = { minor:'var(--kelly)', major:'var(--warn)', crisis:'var(--danger)' };
  el.innerHTML = filtered.slice().reverse().map(i => `
    <div style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-soft);padding:10px 16px;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px">
      <div style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px">
        <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--kelly-deep);background:rgba(45,125,58,0.1);padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px">${i.code}</div>
        ${i.iep ? '<div style="font-size:9px;color:var(--warn);font-weight:700;margin-top:2px;text-align:center">IEP/504</div>' : ''}
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:0">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:3px">
          <span style="font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text)">${i.type}</span>
          <span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--muted)">${i.date}${i.time ? ' · ' + i.time : ''}</span>
          ${i.severity ? `<span style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:${sevColor[i.severity]||'var(--text-mid)'};background:rgba(0,0,0,0.04);padding:1px 7px;border-radius:10px">${i.severity.toUpperCase()}</span>` : ''}
          ${i.parentContact ? '<span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--kelly)">📞 Parent contacted</span>' : ''}
        </div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:var(--text-mid);line-height:1.4">
          ${i.location ? `<span>📍 ${i.location}</span>  ` : ''}${i.grade ? `<span>Grade ${i.grade}</span>` : ''}
        </div>
        ${i.antecedent ? `<div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:3px;line-height:1.4"><strong>Before:</strong> ${i.antecedent}</div>` : ''}
        ${i.response ? `<div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.4"><strong>Response:</strong> ${i.response}</div>` : ''}
        ${i.notes ? `<div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);font-style:italic;line-height:1.4">${i.notes}</div>` : ''}
      </div>
      <button onclick="deleteIncident(${i.id})" style="background:none;border:none;color:var(--muted);cursor:pointer;font-size:14px;flex-shrink:0;padding:2px 4px" title="Delete">×</button>
    </div>`).join('');
}

function deleteIncident(id) {
  incidents = incidents.filter(i => i.id !== id);
  renderIncidentLog();
  updateBehaviorStats();
  updateBadge('badge-behavior', incidents.length);
  syncMobBehaviorBadge(incidents.length);
}

function clearBehaviorLog() {
  if (!incidents.length) return;
  if (!confirm('Clear all incidents from this session?')) return;
  incidents = [];
  renderIncidentLog();
  updateBehaviorStats();
  updateBadge('badge-behavior', 0);
  syncMobBehaviorBadge(0);
  showToast('Log cleared');
}

function updateBehaviorStats() {
  document.getElementById('beh-stat-total').textContent = incidents.length;
  const odrCount = incidents.filter(i => i.severity === 'major' || i.severity === 'crisis').length;
  document.getElementById('beh-stat-odr').textContent = odrCount;
  const codeCounts = {};
  incidents.forEach(i => { codeCounts[i.code] = (codeCounts[i.code] || 0) + 1; });
  const flagged = Object.values(codeCounts).filter(c => c >= 3).length;
  document.getElementById('beh-stat-flagged').textContent = flagged;
  document.getElementById('beh-stat-students').textContent = Object.keys(codeCounts).length;
  // Update dashboard if visible
